&lt;p&gt;BuildOps is a modern, AI-native operational platform built specifically for commercial contractors. We connect field operations, projects, and back-office functions to create a single source of truth for the business, with deep integrations into customers’ accounting systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Role Overview&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;Integration Solutions Architect (ISA)&lt;/strong&gt; ensures seamless financial and data integrations between BuildOps and customers’ accounting systems, with a focus on accuracy, data integrity, and long‑term scalability. You will own accounting integration discovery, design, configuration, testing, and validation, serving as the bridge between Implementation, Product/Engineering, and customers’ finance teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is ideal for someone with &lt;strong&gt;controller-level accounting expertise&lt;/strong&gt; who loves solving complex integration problems, partnering consultatively with customers, and influencing stakeholders toward best practices.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Lead Accounting &amp;amp; Integration Discovery&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead structured discovery sessions with customer finance and accounting teams to understand &lt;strong&gt;GL structure, entities, dimensions/classes, and reporting needs&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document current-state accounting setups and integration workflows, including limitations, dependencies, and custom mapping requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align closely with Solutions Architects and Data Analysts on workflow touchpoints and data requirements across implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Design &amp;amp; Configure Accounting Integrations&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define field mappings, sync direction, and integration logic between BuildOps and accounting platforms (e.g., &lt;strong&gt;QuickBooks Online, Sage Intacct, Vista, Spectrum&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish configuration standards for GL accounts, entities/departments, classes/dimensions, and tax rules within BuildOps and the connected ERP.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and validate integrations in collaboration with Implementation Managers and customers’ accounting teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Test, Validate, and Troubleshoot&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and execute integration test plans for &lt;strong&gt;AP (bills/expenses), AR (invoices/credits), POs, payments, and related workflows&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reconcile data between BuildOps and the accounting system, ensuring accurate end‑to‑end financial results prior to go‑live.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Data Analysts to validate import/export data and resolve discrepancies, documenting root causes and resolutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Consult, Influence, and Advocate Best Practices&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the &lt;strong&gt;trusted integration advisor&lt;/strong&gt; to customers, recommending BuildOps and accounting best practices that support their business today and set them up for future scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balance empathy for customer constraints with clear guidance on standards, data hygiene, and process changes needed for a stable integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop standardized recommendations and playbooks for recurring integration issues and patterns to drive consistency across accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Collaborate Across Product and Customer Teams&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document integration gaps, product limitations, and bugs; propose and escalate solutions to Product and Engineering as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide clear integration documentation and handoffs to Customer Success and Support for post‑go‑live stability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Key Outcomes&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role looks like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Successful end‑to‑end sync validation

