&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Job&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At BuildOps, we&#39;re building a groundbreaking software solution designed to empower today&#39;s commercial contractors. From service management to project execution, we&#39;re reimagining how our customers operate. Our team thrives on ambition, innovation, and collaboration—qualities we look for in every new hire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Product Designer&lt;/strong&gt;, you will play a pivotal role in owning key initiatives and product areas, driving impact through end-to-end design work that helps build and improve critical parts of the product for our customers. Reporting to the &lt;strong&gt;Head of Design&lt;/strong&gt;, this role is perfect for someone who is energized by complex, ambiguous problems in a fast-paced environment and eager to grow with a well-funded, fast-moving startup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently own the end-to-end design process, from user flow diagrams to polished designs that are ready for engineering handoff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in discovery calls and visits with our users, synthesizing research into key insights that support your decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with product managers throughout the design process to deliver solutions that bring value to our users and our business&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with engineers, QA, and other stakeholders to understand requirements and constraints, and iterate on ideas quickly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in design reviews by sharing your work and providing constructive feedback to other team members&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the design team&#39;s culture of collaboration and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor junior members of the team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We Look For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in product design, with a proven track record of delivering successful products from concept to launch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working on enterprise or vertical SaaS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert proficiency in Figma&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of UX/UI principles and methodologies, with experience conducting user research and usability testing, and making data-driven decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and presentation skills, with the ability to articulate design concepts and rationale to diverse audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency with AI tools (e.g., Figma Make, Claude Code) to enhance various stages of the design process—synthesis, ideation, and prototyping&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to travel up to six times per year for team meetings and customer visits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the commercial trades (HVAC, plumbing, electrical) and/or construction, preferred but not required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of HTML and CSS principles, preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with tools like Dovetail and Jira, preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable navigating complex and ambiguous projects in a fast-paced environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A self-starter who is hard-working and naturally takes initiative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented in everything you do&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passionate about design, with a relentless commitment to creating exceptional user experiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Someone who cares deeply about doing excellent work that helps make people&#39;s lives better&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative and supportive, contributing to a strong team culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
